1 16. Child pornography or aggravated child pornography as
2 defined in Section 1021.2, 1021.3, 1024.1, 1024.2 or 1040.12a of
3 this title;
4 17. Child sex trafficking as defined in Section 1030 of this
5 title;
6 18. Lewd molestation of a child as defined in Section 1123 of
7 this title;
8 19. Abuse of a vulnerable adult as defined in Section 10-103 of
9 Title 43A of the Oklahoma Statutes;
10 20. Aggravated trafficking as provided for in subsection C of
11 Section 2-415 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
12 21. Aggravated assault and battery upon any person defending
13 another person from assault and battery; or
14 22. Human trafficking as provided for in Section 748 of this
15 title;
16 23. Domestic abuse by strangulation as provided for in Section
17 644 of this title;
18 24. Domestic assault and battery with a deadly weapon as
19 provided for in Section 644 of this title; and
20 25. Aggravated assault and battery upon a law officer as
21 provided for in Section 650 of this title,
22 shall be required to serve not less than eighty-five percent (85%)
23 of any sentence of imprisonment imposed by the judicial system prior
24 to becoming eligible for consideration for parole. Persons
